《德军总部：新秩序》上市后获得大量好评，[[Metacritic|Metacritic]]根据媒体对游戏各平台的评分，计算出的平均分为：Windows版81/100分<ref name="MCPC" />，Xbox One和PlayStation 4版79/100分<ref name="MCXONE" /><ref name="MCPS4" />。[[GameRankings|GameRankings]]的统计结果为：Windows版84/100分<ref name="GRPC" />，Xbox One版82/100分<ref name="GRXONE" />，PlayStation 4版81/100分<ref name="GRPS4" />。评论员大都喜欢游戏的概念，剧情和战斗机制。

游戏的战斗机制获得一致好评，[[GameSpot|GameSpot]]的丹尼尔·辛德斯（Daniel Hindes）认为，本作战斗机制的多样性和紧张感为系列带来“新的气息”，同时游戏成功的达到了先前他对游戏系列的期望<ref name="GameSpot review" />，{{le|Metro (英国报纸)|Metro (British newspaper)|Metro}}的大卫·詹金斯（David Jenkins）说游戏中的战斗是“实打实”，并称其为近年来最佳单人射击游戏之一<ref name="Metro review" />，而[[GamesRadar|GamesRadar]]的瑞安·塔尔乔尼克（Ryan Taljonick）评价其“令人满意”<ref name="GamesRadar review" />，[[VideoGamer.com|VideoGamer.com]]的西蒙·米勒（Simon Miller）则称赞游戏的射击和潜行机制，并谓前者之“相当不错”<ref name="VideoGamer.com review" />。同样地，GameSpot的辛德斯指出潜行“简单而有效”，认为这是游戏中最好的模式之一<ref name="GameSpot review" />，《卫报》的史蒂夫·鲍克瑟（Steve Boxer）也称潜行是“体面”的行为<ref name="Guardian review" />。

[[IGN|IGN]]的柯林·莫里亚蒂（Colin Moriarty）认为剧情和人物是游戏“真正的亮点”<ref name="IGN review" />，Metro的詹金斯也称赞游戏剧情，指出“音调的搭配匪夷所思，但显然是有意的”<ref name="Metro review" />。《[[电脑与电子游戏|电脑与电子游戏]]》的马特·吉尔曼（Matt Sakuraoka-Gilman）表示剧情是“聪明的剧本，出色的配音，高质量的润色”<ref name="CVG review">{{cite web |url=http://www.computerandvideogames.com/464226/wolfenstein-the-new-order-review/ |title=Wolfenstein The New Order Review: Big and ballsy - but with brains for backup |last=Sakuraoka-Gilman |first=Matt |work=[[Computer_and_Video_Games|Computer and Video Games]] |publisher=[[Future_plc|Future plc]] |date=2014-05-20 |accessdate=2014-08-23 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2Yvjlra?url=http://www.computerandvideogames.com/464226/wolfenstein-the-new-order-review/ |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref>。[[Kotaku|Kotaku]]的迈克·费伊（Mike Fahey）觉得故事情节有些分离，最初的情感表达太明显，但最终令人满意，并称其为“壮观”，他也赞扬了游戏中对B.J的刻画<ref name="Kotaku review">{{cite web |last=Fahey |first=Mike |date=2014-05-21 |url=http://kotaku.com/wolfenstein-the-new-order-the-kotaku-review-1579710698 |title=Wolfenstein: The New Order: The Kotaku Review |work=[[Kotaku|Kotaku]] |publisher={{le|Gawker Media|Gawker Media}} |accessdate=2014-05-26 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2H6SvKn?url=http://kotaku.com/wolfenstein-the-new-order-the-kotaku-review-1579710698 |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref>。GamesRadar的塔尔乔尼克也表示B.J是有趣的人物，但感觉配角不太突出，玩家容易在游戏中忘记他们<ref name="GamesRadar review" />。相反，[[Game_Informer|Game Informer]]的马特·伯兹（Matt Bertz）指出对B.J的残暴行为给予更深入的描写感到奇怪<ref name="GameInformer review" />。VideoGamer.com的米勒也感到了游戏消极的叙述，称这是“可怕的”<ref name="VideoGamer.com review" />。[[Joystiq|Joystiq]]的路德维希·凯泽曼（Ludwig Kietzmann）评论游戏剧情变化太快，当玩家被迫寻找弹药时会感到“拖累”<ref name="Joystiq review" />。{{le|Good Game|Good Game}}的{{le|史蒂芬·奥唐奈|Steven O'Donnell (Australian actor)}}认为否则他会感到是在每次战斗后进行“准备和补充”<ref name="Good Game review">{{cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/tv/goodgame/stories/s4013150.htm |title=Good Game Stories - Wolfenstein: The New Order |first1=奥唐奈 |last1=史蒂芬 |authorlink1= |first2=本迪克森 |last2=斯蒂芬妮 |authorlink2= |work={{le|Good Game|Good Game}} |publisher=[[Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation|Australian Broadcasting Corporation]] |date=2014-05-27 |accessdate=2014-06-12 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2H92b5V?url=http://www.abc.net.au/tv/goodgame/stories/s4013150.htm |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref>。

游戏中采用的虛構历史的概念受到许多评论员的称赞，IGN的莫里亚蒂和Gamespot的的海因斯称它“很有趣”<ref name="GameSpot review" />，前者认为这是游戏的特色之一<ref name="IGN review" />。《[[悉尼先驱晨报|悉尼先驱晨报]]》的杰森·希尔（Jason Hill）称这一设定“引人注目”<ref name="SMH review">{{cite web |url=http://www.smh.com.au/digital-life/games/wolfenstein-the-new-order-review-20140622-zsa3k.html |title=Wolfenstein: The New Order review |last=Hill |first=Jason |work=[[The_Sydney_Morning_Herald|The Sydney Morning Herald]] |publisher={{le|费尔法克斯传媒|Fairfax Media}} |date=2014-06-23 |accessdate=2014-08-23 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2HZHhsv?url=http://www.smh.com.au/digital-life/games/wolfenstein-the-new-order-review-20140622-zsa3k.html |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref>，《[[每日镜报|每日镜报]]》欧文·安斯罗（Owen Anslow）称其“令人着迷”<ref name="Mirror review" />。[[Destructoid|Destructoid]]的克里斯·卡特（Chris Carter）认为开发团队“一路走来”，在游戏概念上倾注了大量时间<ref name="Destructoid review" />。

评论员对游戏的图形设计发表了看法， GameSpot的海因斯称赞了游戏的视觉设计，指出它在准确抓住时间点的同时有效地描绘了游戏的故事情节<ref name="GameSpot review" />。GamesRadar的塔尔乔尼克说游戏的关卡设计有助于他享受射击的乐趣，他也赞扬了关卡的长度，在“某种计划下”可以参与大型枪战<ref name="GamesRadar review" />，Kotaku的费伊也因同样的原因表扬了游戏的关卡，以及游戏的细节表现<ref name="Kotaku review" />。[[數碼間諜|数码间谍]]的利亚姆·马丁（Liam Martin）综合了关于设计的评论，指出人物模型的动画不错，但游戏“几乎不能成为潜在的[[遊戲機歷史_(第八世代)|下一代]]图形设计的榜样”<ref name="Digital Spy review" />。[[澳大利亚广播公司|ABC]]的亚历克斯·沃克（Alex Walker）批评了游戏的图形设计，称开发商“把焦点集中在”游戏的其他方面<ref name="ABC review">{{cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/technology/articles/2014/06/12/4023988.htm |title=Wolfenstein: The New Order Review |last=Walker |first=Alex |work=Technology and Games |publisher=[[Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation|Australian Broadcasting Corporation]] |date=2014-06-12 |accessdate=2014-08-13 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2HBvQPt?url=http://www.abc.net.au/technology/articles/2014/06/12/4023988.htm |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref>。

大多数批评家和评论员都认为，《新秩序》高于他们对德军总部游戏的期望<ref name="IGN review" /><ref name="Mirror review">{{cite web |url=http://www.mirror.co.uk/news/technology-science/technology/wolfenstein-new-order-review---3800952 |title=Wolfenstein: The New Order review - the daddy of First Person Shooters returns to thump some Nazis |last=Anslow |first=Owen |work=[[Daily_Mirror|The Mirror]] |publisher=[[三一镜报|三一镜报]] |date=2014-07-03 |accessdate=2014-08-13 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2HUU06A?url=http://www.mirror.co.uk/news/technology-science/technology/wolfenstein-new-order-review---3800952 |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref><ref name="Forbes review">{{cite web |url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/games/2014/05/23/wolfenstein-the-new-order-review-a-time-to-kill-robot-nazis/ |title='Wolfenstein: The New Order' Review: A Time To Kill Robot Nazis |last=Kain |first=Erik |publisher=''[[Forbes|Forbes]]'' |date=2014-05-23 |accessdate=2014-08-13 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2HG5rIa?url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/games/2014/05/23/wolfenstein-the-new-order-review-a-time-to-kill-robot-nazis/ |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref>。[[官方Xbox杂志|官方Xbox杂志]]的乔恩·布莱思（Jon Blyth）称之为“意想不到的宝石”<ref name="OXM review">{{cite web |url=http://www.totalxbox.com/76661/reviews/wolfenstein-the-new-order-xbox-one-review/ |title=Review: Wolfenstein: The New Order Xbox One |last=Blyth |first=Jon |work=[[官方Xbox杂志|官方Xbox杂志]] |publisher=[[Future_plc|Future plc]] |date=2014-05-20 |accessdate=2014-08-23 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2YISsq0?url=http://www.totalxbox.com/76661/reviews/wolfenstein-the-new-order-xbox-one-review/ |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref>，ABC的沃克也表示他“从来没有如此喜欢过一个游戏”<ref name="ABC review" />。《悉尼先驱晨报》的希尔说游戏可以确保该系列“东山再起”<ref name="SMH review" />， Destructoid的卡特觉得本作在重启系列后没有使用之前的故事设定是一个奇迹<ref name="Destructoid review" />，《[[Edge_(杂志)|Edge]]》杂志也称开发商非常“勇敢”<ref name="Edge review">{{cite web |url=http://www.edge-online.com/review/wolfenstein-the-new-order-review/ |title=Wolfenstein: The New Order review |work=[[Edge_(magazine)|Edge]] |publisher=[[Future_plc|Future plc]] |date=2014-05-28 |accessdate=2014-08-13 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2Hm2rq2?url=http://www.edge-online.com/review/wolfenstein-the-new-order-review/ |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref>。

=== 销售 ===

《德軍總部：新秩序》发行一周之内，成为2014年英国第二畅销游戏，仅次于[[泰坦天降|泰坦天降]]，并且荣登英国周榜，销量占英国游戏总销量的四分之一，总收入的36%<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/wolfenstein-the-new-order-is-the-uk-s-second-biggest-release-of-2014-behind-titanfall/1100-6419896/ |title=Wolfenstein: The New Order is the UK's second-biggest release of 2014, behind Titanfall |last=Makuch |first=Eddie |work=[[GameSpot|GameSpot]] |publisher=[[CBS_Interactive|CBS Interactive]] |date=2014-05-27 |accessdate=2014-06-06 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2HqLd2f?url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/wolfenstein-the-new-order-is-the-uk-s-second-biggest-release-of-2014-behind-titanfall/1100-6419896/ |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref>，根据{{le|家用电脑和电子游戏市场|Market for Home Computing and Video Games|MCV}}的统计，《新秩序》在2014年英国畅销游戏榜中排名第二十二<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mcvuk.com/news/read/revealed-the-100-best-selling-games-of-2014-in-the-uk/0143895 |title=Revealed: The 100 best-selling games of 2014 in the UK |last=Dring |first=Christopher |work={{le|家用电脑和电子游戏市场|Market for Home Computing and Video Games|MCV}} |publisher=Intent Media |date=2015-01-15 |accessdate=2015-02-08 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6WBMuzCZl?url=http://www.mcvuk.com/news/read/revealed-the-100-best-selling-games-of-2014-in-the-uk/0143895 |archivedate=2015-02-08 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref>。在美国，本作分别在2014年5月和6月的畅销榜中排名第四和第七<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/top-10-game-sales-according-to-npd-may-2014-watch-dogs-on-top/1100-6420523/ |title=Top 10 Game Sales According to NPD May 2014, Watch Dogs on Top |last=Haywald |first=Justin |work=[[GameSpot|GameSpot]] |publisher=[[CBS_Interactive|CBS Interactive]] |date=2014-06-16 |accessdate=2014-07-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2HuuO2k?url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/top-10-game-sales-according-to-npd-may-2014-watch-dogs-on-top/1100-6420523/ |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/mario-kart-8-was-best-selling-sku-in-us-for-june-w/1100-6421189/ |title=Mario Kart 8 Was Best-Selling SKU in US for June, Watch Dogs Best-Selling Overall |last=Haywald |first=Justin |work=[[GameSpot|GameSpot]] |publisher=[[CBS_Interactive|CBS Interactive]] |date=2014-07-17 |accessdate=2014-07-23 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2HzN0mp?url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/mario-kart-8-was-best-selling-sku-in-us-for-june-w/1100-6421189/ |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref>，在5月和6月的PS4畅销游戏榜中分别排名第五和第十四<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/may-s-best-selling-psn-games-announced-was-watch-dogs-on-top/1100-6420166/ |title=May's Best-Selling PSN Games Announced -- Was Watch Dogs on Top? |last=Pereira |first=Chris |work=[[GameSpot|GameSpot]] |publisher=[[CBS_Interactive|CBS Interactive]] |date=2014-06-06 |accessdate=2014-06-07 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2I5da7H?url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/may-s-best-selling-psn-games-announced-was-watch-dogs-on-top/1100-6420166/ |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/best-selling-ps4-ps3-and-ps-vita-games-on-psn-in-j/1100-6421003/ |title=Best-Selling PS4, PS3 and PS Vita Games on PSN in June Revealed |last=Pereira |first=Chris |work=[[GameSpot|GameSpot]] |publisher=[[CBS_Interactive|CBS Interactive]] |date=2014-07-09 |accessdate=2014-08-16 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2IDagkT?url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/best-selling-ps4-ps3-and-ps-vita-games-on-psn-in-j/1100-6421003/ |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref>。在日本发行的首周，PS3和PS4版销量分别位于排行榜的第十五和第八，总销量达1万1千套<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.playstationlifestyle.net/2014/06/11/japanese-sales-chart-psp-gets-a-boost-outsells-ps3/ |title=Japanese Sales Chart: PSP Gets a Boost, Outsells PS3 |last=Dunning |first=Jason |work=PlayStation Lifestyle |publisher={{le|CraveOnline|CraveOnline}} |date=2014-06-11 |accessdate=2014-06-14 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2IKUWrH?url=http://www.playstationlifestyle.net/2014/06/11/japanese-sales-chart-psp-gets-a-boost-outsells-ps3/ |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref>。截至2014年6月，本作实体版在欧洲销量近40万套，相当于2100多万欧元<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nintendoeverything.com/europe-2014-top-20-half-year-software-chart-top-10-publishers/ |title=Europe - 2014 top 20 half-year software chart, top 10 publishers |author=Brian |publisher=Nintendo Everything |date=2014-08-13 |accessdate=2014-08-16 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6S2INEjii?url=http://nintendoeverything.com/europe-2014-top-20-half-year-software-chart-top-10-publishers/ |archivedate=2014-08-23 |deadurl=no |language=en }}</ref>。

=== 奖项 ===

《德軍總部：新秩序》获得了{{le|游戏媒体|Video game journalism}}的多个提名和奖项。本作获得{{le|经典游戏室|Classic Game Room}}的{{le|年度游戏奖|List of Game of the Year awards}}，以及[[金摇杆奖|金摇杆奖]]<ref name="Golden Joystick Awards" />、{{le|Good Game|Good Game}}<ref name="GGAs 2014" />、[[Game_Informer|Game Informer]]<ref name="Game Informer Awards" />、和[[IGN|IGN]]澳大利亚<ref name="BBSA" />的提名，获得[[Polygon|Polygon]]奖项的亚军<ref name="Polygon GOTY" />。游戏也被纳入2014年各种媒体的最佳游戏列表：[[今日美国|今日美国]]将其列为第九名<ref name="USA Today" />，[[Eurogamer|Eurogamer]]列为第十<ref name="Eurogamer Top 50" />，[[Ars_Technica|Ars Technica]]列为第六<ref name="ArsTech" />。本作也获得{{le|Cheat Code Central|Cheat Code Central}}<ref name="Cody Awards" />、[[The_Escapist|The Escapist]]<ref name="Escapist Awards" />、[[游戏大奖|游戏大奖]]<ref name="Game Awards" />、Game Informer<ref name="Game Informer Shooter" />、[[GameTrailers|GameTrailers]]<ref name="GameTrailers Awards" />、[[Hardcore_Gamer|Hardcore Gamer]]<ref name="Hardcore Gamer Awards" />和IGN<ref name="IGN Best Shooter" />的最佳射击游戏提名，因其精彩的游戏剧情，被游戏大奖<ref name="Game Awards" />、金摇杆奖<ref name="Golden Joystick Awards" />、IGN澳大利亚<ref name="BBSA" />和[[西南偏南|西南偏南]]游戏奖提名<ref name="SXSW" />。游戏获得了[[Giant_Bomb|Giant Bomb]]<ref name="Giant Bomb" />和[[Kotaku|Kotaku]]读者<ref name="Kotaku Surprise" />的惊喜大奖的亚军，IGN澳大利亚的最佳PC游戏<ref name="BBSA" />，Kotaku读者的最佳PC游戏的亚军<ref name="Kotaku PC GOTY" />。游戏被Hardcore Gamer提名为最佳多平台游戏<ref name="Hardcore Gamer Awards" />，被IGN澳大利亚提名为最佳游戏机游戏<ref name="BBSA" />，被3 Game提名为最佳PlayStation 3游戏<ref name="IGN Best PS3" />，被IGN提名为最佳Xbox 360游戏<ref name="IGN Best 360" />，最佳Xbox One游戏<ref name="IGN Best XBONE" />。

